content.description: Scramble up into an overhang, find good jams, and use a left-foot ledge to pull yourself into the crack. A few more jams gets you to the anchors.
content.location: Furthest right route on the wall.

content.description:
Start on a dirty ledge.  Reach up and slot a hand jam to pull yourself over the roof/bulge. couple more hand jams to work the feet up. Walk off on top.

Can use the tree or other nature anchor to belay second up to clean the route.
content.location: Towards right end of wall. Under an overhang with dirty ledge that starts the route.

content.description: Start with a few bouldery moves to the first bolt. 3 more bolts on thin, slabby rock leads to shiny perma-draw anchors.
A steep move into a crack leads to face climbing on the left side of 2 bolts above.  Bolted anchor at the top.
content.protection:
2 bolts and gear to 1.5"

bolted anchor
content.location: Approaching from the right, this is the second bolted line. It is approximately in the middle of the main portion of the wall.

content.description: The route starts off in a crack in a arÃªte which you can jam or lieback out of it, The crux is getting out of the crack onto the face  then head up and right to the anchors.
content.protection: Pro to 1.5" Shares same anchor as Talking turkeys and Marshmellow chicks
content.location:
Between TALKING TURKEY and BARLEY HANGING ON.

Obvious crack system .

content.description: Climb smooth, thin holds for first 10 feet.
content.location: Route to the right of Klokeism

content.description:
Start below the nice flake with underclings in the middle of the face between "Washing the Elephant" and "Just Barely Hanging On", climb up past a single bolt, then head up and right to the "Just Barely..." anchors.

Crux is around the bolt, positive holds the whole way but may take a minute to find them. Actually a pretty interesting route if you're already in the area.
content.protection: 1 bolt, small gear above that?? (only TR-soloed this route, not sure of exact gear, feel free to update)
content.location: Face between "Washing the Elephant" and "Just Barely Hanging On" at left end of the "sitting log".

content.description: Starts on a crack and climbs up to a ledge where you need to mantle. 4 ft below the anchor is a bulge which you have to navigate your way out to the anchors,( the crux)
content.protection: 2 bolts plus gear to 0.5" Bolted anchors at top. Some slings are useful for anchor
content.location: Route is dirty with some wheats on it.

content.description:
Follow cracks and pockets that angle left to the anchors.

4 bolts have been added as "Birthday Boy", but can easily be clipped from this route.
content.protection: 4 bolts pro to 1", bolted anchor with draws
content.location: Starts under chunky overhanging section beneath crack; up and over the left edge of overhang and shifting back right seemed easier than directly up through the mini-dihedral with the bolt.

content.description: Climb smooth section between two cracks and stay right of the bolts. " Difficulty depends where you go"
content.protection: 3 bolts and pro to 2", bolted anchor with draws
content.location: middle of the wall, to the right of the bolts

content.description: Start to the left of a dead tree? Climb over the bulge on smooth rock, then up slab. the diagonal crack provides protection.
content.location: look for the dead tree on the left of the wall.

content.description: There is a boulder move at the bottom where you can jam and lieback. From there Climb up to a small ledge where you rest then traverse left on decent holds to the top.
content.protection: There are two bolts , pro to 0.5" The anchor is made of two bolts,slings for anchors. Shares same anchor as talking turkey.
content.location: the route is in the middle between talking turkeys and wuddel

content.description: First bolt can be clipped from the ground.  Start on the face directly under the bolt.  Move up the face trending towards the arete. Move to the face after clipping the second.  Then up to the anchors.
content.protection:
2 Bolts

Optional: Small cam to protect the final move to anchor. As a fall here one could deck.
content.location: On left side of wall, around first corner coming from access trail

climbs.name: Just Barely Hanging On
climbs.fa: R. McPhee, B. Roberts, D. Like 2004

content.description: A short slab section leads up to a ledge.  A few steep moves above the ledge reach the anchors.  There is a bolted anchor at the top.
content.location: On the main portion of the wall, this is the farthest bolted line on the left.  It is just to the right of an alcove.

content.description: spooky top out after 18' of crack climbing
content.location: look in the corner around the left side of the main wall.

climbs.name: The Gift that Keeps On Giving

content.description: From the top of a sharp rock, jam a short crack then move up to a large sloping ledge
content.protection: pro to 2", bolted anchor with draws
content.location: just to the left of the two cracks on the right side of the wall
